<!--Ryō no Gige--><!--Ryō no Gige--><!--Ryō no Gige--><!--Ryō no Gige--><!--Ryō no Gige--><!--Ryō no Gige-->

{{Nihon no hō}}
'''Ryō no Gige''' (令義解) is an interpretive text of the {{ill|Yōrō Code|ja|養老令|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, created to establish precise guidelines<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|和書|title=令義解 凡例|year=1939|publisher=新訂増補 国史大系 第22巻|page=1|author=黒板|url=https://dl.ndl.go.jp/pid/3431635/1/108}}</ref>. It was compiled in 833 CE ({{ill|Tenchō|ja|天長|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 10) under an imperial edict from Emperor Junna, with the right minister {{ill|Kiyohara no Natsuno|ja|清原夏野|qq=draft|qq=draft}} serving as chief editor. The compilation involved 12 notable scholars, including {{ill|Sugawara no Kiyotomo|ja|菅原清公|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Sanuki no Emanari|ja|讃岐永直|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and others<ref>{{Cite book|和書|title=令義解序|publisher= |series=新訂増補 国史大系|volume=第22|url=https://dl.ndl.go.jp/pid/3431635/1/118|author=黒板}}</ref>. The work originally comprised 30 articles across 10 volumes<ref name=":0" />, but only 21 articles remain extant. Seven of these can be extracted from the {{ill|Ryōshū Gige|ja|令集解|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and additional fragments of two articles have been collected since the early modern period. Modern editions, including those from the {{ill|National Historical Series|ja|国史大系|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, incorporate these reconstructed texts.

Since the {{ill|Yōrō Code|ja|養老令|qq=draft|qq=draft}} has been lost, the ''Ryō no Gige'' serves as a critical source for the transmission of both the {{ill|Taihō Code|ja|大宝律令|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and the Yōrō Code<ref name=":0" />. Unlike the ''{{ill|Ryōshū Gige|ja|令集解|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'', a private commentary compiled by {{ill|Wemune Naomoto|ja|惟宗直本|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the ''Ryō no Gige'' was an officially sanctioned commentary with legal authority.

The structure of the text presents the original law in bold characters, with the interpretive commentary added in smaller, double-spaced text between the lines.

== Compilers ==
* Hanbe no Matsunaga (漢部松長) – {{ill|Daishoi|ja|大初位|1=Greater Initial Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Lower, {{ill|Myōbōtokugyōshō|ja|明法得業生|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* Kawakare Katsunari (川枯勝成) – {{ill|Jūhachi-i|ja|従八位|1=Junior Eighth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} U11er, Minor Official of {{ill|Gyōbushō|ja|刑部省|1=Ministry of Justice (pre-modern Japan)|lt=Ministry of Justice|qq= (pre-modern Japan)|1=Ministry of Justice (pre-modern Japan)|lt=Ministry of Justice|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* {{ill|Sanuki no Emanari|ja|讃岐永直|qq=draft|qq=draft}} – {{ill|Jūrokui|ja|従六位|1=Junior Sixth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Lower, Left Recorder, {{ill|Myōbōhakase|ja|明法博士|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* {{ill|Ono no Takamura|ja|小野篁|qq=draft|qq=draft}} – {{ill|Jūgoin|ja|従五位|1=Junior Fifth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Lower, Minor Governor of {{ill|Dazaifu|ja|大宰府|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* Zendo no Masada (善道真貞) – {{ill|Shōgoi|ja|正五位|1=Senior Fifth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Lower, Governor of {{ill|Awa Province|ja|阿波国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* Okiwara Toshihisa (興原敏久) – {{ill|Shōgoi|ja|正五位|1=Senior Fifth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} U11er, Senior Judge of {{ill|Gyōbushō|ja|刑部省|1=Ministry of Justice (pre-modern Japan)|lt=Ministry of Justice|qq= (pre-modern Japan)|1=Ministry of Justice (pre-modern Japan)|lt=Ministry of Justice|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* Fujiwara no Mamoru (藤原衛) – {{ill|Jūshii|ja|従四位|1=Junior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Lower, Vice Minister of {{ill|Gyōbushō|ja|刑部省|1=Ministry of Justice (pre-modern Japan)|lt=Ministry of Justice|qq= (pre-modern Japan)|1=Ministry of Justice (pre-modern Japan)|lt=Ministry of Justice|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* Fujiwara no Uton (藤原雄敏) – {{ill|Jūshii|ja|従四位|1=Junior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Lower, Senior Official of {{ill|Kageyushō|ja|勘解由使|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* {{ill|Sugawara no Kiyokimi|ja|菅原清公|qq=draft|qq=draft}} – {{ill|Shōshii|ja|正四位|1=Senior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Lower, {{ill|Left Kyoto District Governor|ja|左京大夫|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* {{ill|Fujiwara no Tsunatsugu|ja|藤原常嗣|qq=draft|qq=draft}} – {{ill|Jūshii|ja|従四位|1=Junior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Lower, {{ill|Councilor|ja|参議|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* Minabuchi no Hirozane (南淵弘貞) – {{ill|Jūsanmi|ja|従三位|1=Junior Third Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Councilor
* {{ill|Kiyohara no Natsuno|ja|清原夏野|qq=draft|qq=draft}} – {{ill|Shōsanmi|ja|正三位|1=Senior Third Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Udaijin|ja|右大臣|qq=draft|qq=draft}}

