<!--Ryō no Gige--><!--Ryō no Gige--><!--Ryō no Gige--><!--Ryō no Gige--><!--Ryō no Gige--><!--Ryō no Gige--> [[Category:9th-century books]] [[Category:Heian-period books]] [[Category:Japanese Imperial Edicts]] [[Category:Historical jurisprudence in Japan]] [[Category:Law books]] [[Category:Commentaries]] [[Category:Emperor Junna]] <!--jawiki derived wikidata interwikis--> [[it:Ryō no Gige]] [[ko:영의해]]

{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11378320]] Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 08:58, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{Nihon no hō}} '''Ryō no Gige''' (令義解) is an interpretive text of the {{ill|Yōrō Code|ja|養老令|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yōrō Code|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 養老律令}}, created to establish precise guidelines<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|和書|title=令義解 凡例|year=1939|publisher=新訂増補 国史大系 第22巻|page=1|author=黒板|url=https://dl.ndl.go.jp/pid/3431635/1/108}}</ref>. It was compiled in 833 CE ([[:en:Tenchō|Tenchō]] 10) under an imperial edict from Emperor Junna, with the right minister {{ill|Kiyohara no Natsuno|ja|清原夏野|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kiyohara no Natsuno|qq=}} serving as chief editor. The compilation involved 12 notable scholars, including [[:en:Sugawara no Kiyotomo|Sugawara no Kiyotomo]], {{ill|Sanuki no Emanari|ja|讃岐永直|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sanuki no Emanari|qq=}}, and others<ref>{{Cite book|和書|title=令義解序|publisher= |series=新訂増補 国史大系|volume=第22|url=https://dl.ndl.go.jp/pid/3431635/1/118|author=黒板}}</ref>. The work originally comprised 30 articles across 10 volumes<ref name=":0" />, but only 21 articles remain extant. Seven of these can be extracted from the {{ill|Ryōshū Gige|ja|令集解|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ryōshū Gige|qq=}}, and additional fragments of two articles have been collected since the early modern period. Modern editions, including those from the {{ill|National Historical Series|ja|国史大系|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/National Historical Series|qq=}}, incorporate these reconstructed texts.
Since the {{ill|Yōrō Code|ja|養老令|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yōrō Code|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 養老律令}} has been lost, the ''Ryō no Gige'' serves as a critical source for the transmission of both the [[:en:Taihō Code|Taihō Code]] and the Yōrō Code<ref name=":0" />. Unlike the ''{{ill|Ryōshū Gige|ja|令集解|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ryōshū Gige|qq=}}'', a private commentary compiled by {{ill|Wemune Naomoto|ja|惟宗直本|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wemune Naomoto|qq=}}, the ''Ryō no Gige'' was an officially sanctioned commentary with legal authority.
The structure of the text presents the original law in bold characters, with the interpretive commentary added in smaller, double-spaced text between the lines.
